<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Rustle" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Rustle,</orth> to make a noise like the rubbing of silk or straw: <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 98</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 24</bibl>. In <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.304" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 304</bibl> Qq <emph>the winds do sorely russel,</emph> Ff <emph>ruffle.</emph> In <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 68</bibl> Mrs. Quickly <emph>rushle.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>